.TH MULTIFLEXI\-EXECUTOR 8 "June 2026" "multiflexi-executor 1.16.0" "MultiFlexi"
.SH NAME
multiflexi\-executor \- execute a MultiFlexi job or run a RunTemplate
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B multiflexi\-executor
.B \-j
.I JOB_ID
.RB [ \-e
.IR ENV_FILE ]
.RB [ \-o
.IR OUTPUT_FILE ]
.br
.B multiflexi\-executor
.B \-r
.I RUNTEMPLATE_ID
.RB [ \-t
.IR SECONDS ]
.RB [ \-e
.IR ENV_FILE ]
.RB [ \-o
.IR OUTPUT_FILE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B multiflexi\-executor
runs a single MultiFlexi job either by executing an existing job record
inline
.RB ( \-j ),
or by creating a new job from a RunTemplate, queueing it for immediate
execution and waiting for the daemon to run it
.RB ( \-r ).
.PP
It is designed for one-shot execution.
For continuous, daemon-mode operation (polling the schedule queue and
launching jobs automatically) see the
.B multiflexi\-executor
systemd service, which runs
.I /usr/share/multiflexi-executor/daemon.php
in the background.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-j " JOB_ID" ", \-\-job=" JOB_ID
Execute an existing job identified by its numeric database ID, inline.
This is the path the daemon uses to launch each due job.
.TP
.BI \-r " RUNTEMPLATE_ID" ", \-\-runtemplate=" RUNTEMPLATE_ID
Create a new job from the given RunTemplate, queue it for immediate
execution and block until the daemon has run it. The job's standard
output, standard error and exit code are then reproduced by this command.
The daemon must be running for the job to be picked up.
.TP
.BI \-t " SECONDS" ", \-\-timeout=" SECONDS
With
.BR \-r ,
maximum time to wait for the daemon to execute the queued job.
.B 0
waits indefinitely.
Defaults to the value of
.B RUNTEMPLATE_WAIT_TIMEOUT
or
.BR 300 .
On timeout the command exits 124.
.TP
.BI \-o " FILE" ", \-\-output=" FILE
Write captured job output to
.IR FILE
instead of stdout.
Defaults to the value of
.B RESULT_FILE
or
.IR php://stdout .
.TP
.BI \-e " FILE" ", \-\-environment=" FILE
Path to the
.I .env
configuration file.
Defaults to
.I ../.env
relative to the script.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DB_CONNECTION
Database driver:
.BR mysql ", " pgsql ", " sqlite " (default: mysql)"
.TP
.B DB_HOST / DB_PORT / DB_DATABASE / DB_USERNAME / DB_PASSWORD
Database connection parameters.
.TP
.B APP_DEBUG
Set to
.B true
to enable verbose console logging.
.TP
.B MULTIFLEXI_DAEMONIZE
Set to
.B false
to run the daemon for a single cycle then exit.
.TP
.B MULTIFLEXI_CYCLE_PAUSE
Seconds the daemon sleeps between polling cycles (default:
.BR 10 ).
.TP
.B MULTIFLEXI_MAX_PARALLEL
Maximum number of concurrently running job subprocesses.
.B 0
means unlimited (default:
.BR 0 ).
.TP
.B MULTIFLEXI_MEMORY_LIMIT_MB
Soft memory ceiling in megabytes.
The daemon initiates a graceful shutdown when usage approaches this value.
.B 0
disables the check (default:
.BR 0 ).
.TP
.B RESULT_FILE
Default output destination for one-shot runs (default:
.IR php://stdout ).
.TP
.B RUNTEMPLATE_WAIT_TIMEOUT
Default timeout, in seconds, for
.B \-r
to wait for the daemon to finish the queued job.
.B 0
waits indefinitely (default:
.BR 300 ).
Overridden by
.BR \-t .
.TP
.B RUNTEMPLATE_WAIT_POLL
Interval, in seconds, between database polls while
.B \-r
waits for completion (default:
.BR 2 ).
.SH DAEMON BEHAVIOUR
When run as a systemd service, the daemon polls the
.B schedule
table every
.B MULTIFLEXI_CYCLE_PAUSE
seconds.
For each due job it:
.IP 1. 3
Checks whether another job from the same RunTemplate is already running.
If so, the schedule entry is left untouched and picked up in a later cycle.
This prevents duplicate side-effects (e.g.\& double bank-statement imports)
when a long-running job overlaps its next scheduled trigger.
.IP 2.
Claims the schedule entry by deleting it, then launches
.I executor.php
as an isolated subprocess with its own database connection and memory space.
.IP 3.
Waits for all in-flight subprocesses to finish before exiting when it
receives
.B SIGTERM
or
.B SIGINT
(requires the
.B pcntl
PHP extension).
.SH EXIT STATUS
The exit code of a one-shot run mirrors the exit code returned by the job
process itself.
With
.BR \-r ,
the command exits
.B 124
if the timeout elapses before the daemon completes the job.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/multiflexi/multiflexi.env
Runtime environment configuration.
.TP
.I /usr/share/multiflexi-executor/daemon.php
Continuous daemon script managed by systemd.
.TP
.I /usr/share/multiflexi-executor/executor.php
One-shot execution script called by this binary.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR multiflexi-run-template (1),
.BR multiflexi-scheduler (8)
